            Welfare
        </h2>
        <i class="accordion-item__header-icon"><i aria-hidden="true" class="btn__icon fa-sharp fa-regular fa-arrow-down"></i><span class="btn__text" data-text-content=""></span></i>
    </button>
    <div class="accordion-item__body collapse"
         id="collapse-15777192"
         aria-labelledby="heading-15777192">
        <div class="accordion-item__content rte theme-zone theme--cloud">
            <p>The Army offers a wide range of welfare services for its Regular, Reserve, Civilian and Contractor personnel. This ranges from financial, medical, wellbeing, and family support. The page below provide further information on the options available including Unit Welfare Support, Army Welfare Service, Army Related Charities, and support for Civil Servants. In the case of an emergency, please contact 999 in the first instance or if you experience a serious illness or death in your family, you should call Joint Casualty and Compassionate Centre (JCCC) on 01452 519951.</p>

<a data-target-content-id="2256" href="/support-and-training/welfare/" class="nav-link cta-btn cta-btn--primary"><span class="cta-btn__bg"></span><span class="cta-btn__text">
