        <div class="accordion-item__content rte theme-zone theme--cloud">
            <p>The UK Government defines a veteran as someone who has served for at least one day in the UK Armed Forces (as a Regular or Reservist).</p>
<p>There is a range of support available for our Service Leavers to support them through the transition to civilian life and beyond. Visit the Service Leavers &amp; Veterans page to find out more.</p>

